        keyPoints: ["Hesselbach's triangle: inferior epigastric artery (lateral), rectus (medial), inguinal ligament (inferior)", "Indirect hernia: through deep ring, lateral to IEA, can reach scrotum", "Direct hernia: through Hesselbach's triangle, medial to IEA, rarely reaches scrotum", "Femoral hernia: most prone to strangulation, more common in females", "Indirect hernia is more common (80%) and has congenital basis (patent processus vaginalis)"],
